===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|牙|邑|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=town; city}}.

The semantic component suggests that this character was originally used in a place name, which ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' suggests to be {{zh-l|*琅邪}}. It was later borrowed for other meanings, the most prominent being “wrong; evil” (originally written as {{zh-l|衺}}).

